args: It's further to the right, Estelle!
You've gone too far right!\nGo back to the left!
No, the other way! Turn around a bit...\nOkay, now to the right!
Don't listen to a word he says!\nJust keep goin' straight!
Oh, for the love of... Whose instructions\nam I supposed to believe?!
There's a pitfall ahead of you!\nJump over it!
Now you're just lying to me!
Take one step to the right... That's it!\nNow swing your stick down!
Yep. You cracked that watermelon\nclean in half.
Everybody gather 'round and dig in!\nOh, but save the big chunk for Estelle.
I know you've never done this before,\nbut this IS pretty fun, yeah?
What are you doing up there\non that pile of sand?

It's a game! Pretty much like
King of the Mountain, but you
can only push with your hands.
Speaking of which...you're up!
Yep! You and I are gonna wrestle\nand see who comes out on top!
Aw, it's just sand—plus it's only as\nhigh as our knees. You'll be fine!
Come on! You can do this, Estelle!
Teach that Luca a lesson\nhe'll not soon forget!
Eeek! I'll get you for that!
Nice! But I'm a pro when it comes to\ngames, so you'll have to do better!
I'll have you know, I was quite\nthe little tomboy as a child.
I'm not surprised—they've really been\nkeeping you busy.
Yes, but I still had a lot of fun.
Good! I was a little worried you were\nonly playing along because you felt\npressured to.
Not at all. At first, of course, I was a little\nreluctant, but before I knew it,\nI was enjoying myself. Still...
You said that what I really needed\nwas to play with all of you and just\nforget my cares, right?
But I'm not certain how that meshes\nwith my concerns about good behavior.
Well, you broke open a watermelon, right?
And you touched Luca while you were\nplaying King of the Mountain, right?
Yes, I did that as well.
Which means you did things you said\nwere inappropriate and dangerous before.
Are you appalled at your own behavior?
Then maybe those things aren't\nquite so bad as you first thought.
I think you just didn't know how\nmuch fun the beach could be.
That's why you weren't able to draw\na line between what's done for fun\nand what isn't.
You didn't know what was good and what\nwas bad, so you just defaulted to thinking\nof EVERYTHING as bad.
...By Ilia, I think you're right.\nHow did I not realize that before?
But now that you know what it feels like\nto have fun, you won't have that problem.
If you're still not feeling confident,\nthat just means you need to hang out\nwith us even MORE.
Estelle! Where's my rematch?!\nI'M GONNA TAKE YOU DOWN!
...Coming, Luca! But don't be mad\nwhen I defeat you yet again!
